"World in Motion","strBirthLocation":"Therwil BL, Switzerland","strEthnicity":"White","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Benjamin Kevin Siegrist (born 31 January 1992) is a Swiss professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Serie A club Genoa, on loan from Liga I club Rapid București. \r\n He was a member of the Switzerland squad at the 2012 Olympic Games in London and went on to represent the Swiss Under-21s. In 2009, Siegrist was part of his nation's FIFA U-17 World Cup winning side, during which he also received the competition's inaugural Golden Glove award for best goalkeeper. During seven years in the Aston Villa Academy Siegrist undertook a series of short-term loans to English Football League and Conference sides. After a spell in the Swiss Super League with Vaduz, Siegrist signed for Scottish club Dundee United in 2018.\r\n\r\nSiegrist has been part of Switzerland squads at U17, U18, U19, and U21 level. Siegrist won the 2009 FIFA U-17 World Cup in Nigeria with his nation: the goalkeeper was an integral part of the side that beat the hosts in the final and won the tournament's first Golden Glove award as a result. He was chosen as a backup goalkeeper for Switzerland's U21 squad at the 2011 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship, but remained an unused substitute throughout the tournament as Switzerland lost 2–0 in the final to Spain. In 2012, Siegrist was chosen as a backup goalkeeper to Diego Benaglio for Pierluigi Tami's 18-man squad to represent Switzerland at the 2012 London Olympic Games.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Goalkeeper","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.94 m (6 ft 4 in)","strWeight":"185 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/rqc77q1608386078.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/nfibnh1758997678.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/v5j22n1675899771.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Siegrist"},{"idPlayer":"34203485","idTeam":"133675","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"284570","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":"728733","idESPN":"311173","strNationality":"England","strPlayer":"Brooke Norton-Cuffy","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Genoa","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"2004-01-12","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"15","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"2,00 Mln. €","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"Roc Nation Sports","strBirthLocation":"London, England","strEthnicity":"","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Brooke Dion Nelson Norton-Cuffy (born 12 January 2004) is an English professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Genoa.\r\nClub career\r\nNorton-Cuffy began his career with Chelsea, before joining Arsenal at the age of twelve, and signing his first professional contract on 21 January 2021. On 18 January 2022, joined Lincoln City on loan for the remainder of the season. He made his senior debut coming off the bench away to Plymouth Argyle on 22 January 2022. He scored his first senior goal against Sheffield Wednesday on 5 March 2022.\r\n\r\nOn 22 August 2022, he joined Rotherham United on a season-long loan. In January 2023 Norton-Cuffy was recalled by Arsenal, and he moved to Coventry City on loan instead.\r\n\r\nInternational career\r\nHaving already represented England at U16 and U18 level, Norton-Cuffy made his U19 debut during a 3-1 win over Republic of Ireland during 2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification at the Bescot Stadium.\r\n\r\nOn 17 June 2022, Norton-Cuffy was included in the England U19 squad for the 2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship. He was a second-half substitute in the final as England beat Israel 3-1 in extra time to win the tournament.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Defender","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"181 cm","strWeight":"152 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/zwihng1674658072.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/j8o2561758997373.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/9bsyor1758997443.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Norton-Cuffy"},{"idPlayer":"34148287","idTeam":"133675","idTeam2":"0","idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"3430","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":"199953","idESPN":"182071","strNationality":"Italy","strPlayer":"Caleb Ekuban","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Genoa","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":"81","dateBorn":"1994-03-23","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"18","dateSigned":"2013-01-25","strSigning":"1.8 Mln €","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"GB1","strBirthLocation":"Villafranca di Verona, Italy","strEthnicity":"White","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Caleb Ansah Ekuban (born 23 March 1994) is a professional footballer who plays for Genoa as a striker. Born in Italy to Ghanaian parents, Ekuban declared for the Ghana national football team. \r\nEkuban is a striker known for his pace, technical ability and strong physique. His style of play and prolific goal scoring as a youngster in the Chievo youth team saw him likened to compatriot Mario Balotelli.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":"Caleb Ekuban è un calciatore ghanese attaccante del Genoa e della nazionale ghanese.","strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Forward","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"http://www.instagram.com/eku_18/","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.82 m","strWeight":"174 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/4yt7821507559278.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/86au561758989039.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/vr2x7a1630826913.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Ekuban"},{"idPlayer":"34147217","idTeam":"133675","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"779","idPlayerManager":"829412","idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":"5947","idESPN":null,"strNationality":"Italy","strPlayer":"Daniele De Rossi","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Genoa","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":"93","dateBorn":"1983-07-24","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"","dateSigned":"2001-07-01","strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Roma, Italy","strEthnicity":"White","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Daniele De Rossi born 24 July 1983 is an Italian football manager and former professional player, currently in charge as the head coach of Serie A club Genoa.\r\n\r\nDe Rossi made his professional debut with Roma during the 2001–02 season, and made his Serie A debut the following year. With the club, he won the Coppa Italia twice in 2007 and 2008, and the 2007 Supercoppa Italiana. He was named Serie A Young Footballer of the Year in 2006, and the Serie A Italian Footballer of the Year in 2009. De Rossi inherited the captaincy of Roma at the start of the 2017–18 season following the retirement of Francesco Totti, during which he helped Roma to the Champions League semi-final for the first time in the Champions League era. At the end of the 2018–19 season, he left Roma after 18 seasons with the team. With 616 appearances for Roma in all competitions, he is the club's second-most capped player of all time, behind Totti. He subsequently joined Argentine club Boca Juniors in the summer of 2019, and retired from professional football in January of the following year.\r\n\r\nDe Rossi represented Italy at under-19, under-20, under-21 and senior levels, winning the 2004 European Under-21 Football Championship, and also represented Italy at the 2004 Olympics, winning a bronze medal. From his senior international debut in 2004, until his retirement from the national team in 2017, he earned 117 caps, and is Italy's joint fourth-highest capped player of all time, and most capped midfielder of all time. With 21 goals, he is the highest scoring midfielder for Italy post-World War II, and Italy's all-time second most prolific midfielder behind Adolfo Baloncieri. He was part of the 2006 World Cup-winning squad and also participated at Euro 2008, the 2009 Confederations Cup, the 2010 World Cup, Euro 2012 (finishing in second place), the 2013 Confederations Cup (finishing in third place), the 2014 World Cup, and Euro 2016. De Rossi was named in the Euro 2012 Team of the Tournament for his performances.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Manager","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"twitter.com/officialderossi","strInstagram":"www.instagram.com/danielederossi/","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.84 m (6 ft 0 in)","strWeight":"83 kg (183 lb)","intLoved":"1","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/dv7m4e1721804669.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/j6j8eh1721804742.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/hbu60e1721804724.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"Yes","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Rossi"},{"idPlayer":"34220155","idTeam":"133675","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"31445","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":"312773","idESPN":"210391","strNationality":"Italy","strPlayer":"Daniele Sommariva","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Genoa","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"1997-07-18","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"39","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Genova, Italy","strEthnicity":"White","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Daniele Sommaria is an Italian football player, goalkeeper for Genoa.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"st